Shaun Peter Bailey (born 19 February 1990, Norwich) is an English cricketer. He is a right-handed batsman and a right-arm medium-fast bowler who currently plays for Northamptonshire.
Bailey, who made his cricketing debut in the East Anglian Premier Cricket League for Swardeston at the age of thirteen, and who was educated at Hockham School and Wayland Community High School, first played for Northamptonshire's Second XI in the 2005 Second XI Championship. Following an appearance in the 2007 MCCA Trophy, Bailey made his only first-class appearance in 2008. After failing to break into the first team, he left Northamptonshire at the end of the 2009 season.
